metadata.description:
In the shadows of my mind
A flicker of light has died
An ember that once burned bright
Now fades into the night

Burnout, a beast that lingers
A weight that only grows
It feeds on all that's good and pure
And leaves a gaping hole

I see myself, a puppeteer's toy
Controlled by hands unknown
I dance and spin to a tune so dark
As the strings cut through my soul

The world around me twists and turns
In a kaleidoscope of pain
A labyrinth of broken dreams
Where hope has long been slain

Yet in this darkness, there's a spark
A glimmer of something new
A hope that I can rise again
And start my life anew

So I gather up the broken pieces
And put them back in place
I rebuild what's been torn apart
And find a way to face

The burnout beast that once consumed
Is now a thing of the past
I'm stronger now, I've found my way
And the darkness cannot last.
